quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,49,"Had not a Grace from his Lord reached him, he would indeed have been (left in the stomach of the fish, but We forgave him): so he was cast off on the naked shore, while he was to be blamed."
  68,50,"Then his Lord chose him and made him of the righteous."
  68,51,"And verily, those who disbelieve would almost make you slip with their eyes (through hatred) when they hear the Reminder (the Qur’ân), and they say: "
  69,46,"And then We certainly would have cut off his life artery (aorta),"
  69,47,"And none of you could have withheld Us from (punishing) him."
  69,48,"And verily, this (Qur’an) is a Reminder for the Muttaqûn (the pious. See V.2:2)."
  70,40,"So I swear by the Lord of all the [three hundred and sixty-five (365)] points of sunrise and sunset in the east and the west that surely We are Able"
  70,41,"To replace them by (others) better than them; and We are not to be outrun."
  70,42,"So leave them to plunge in vain talk{1} and play about, until they meet their Day which they are promised -",1:[{70:42} See the footnote of {4:5}.]
  74,25,""
  74,26,"I will cast him into Hell-fire.{1}",1:[{74:26} See the footnote of {17:97}.]
  74,27,"And what will make you know (exactly) what Hell-fire is?"
  75,22,"Some faces that Day shall be Nâdirah (shining and radiant)."
  75,23,"Looking at their Lord (Allâh)."
  75,24,"And some faces, that Day, will be Bâsirah (dark, gloomy, frowning, and sad),"
  76,16,"Crystal-clear, made of silver. They will determine the measure thereof (according to their wishes)."
  76,17,"And they will be given to drink there of a cup (of wine) mixed with Zanjabîl (ginger),"
  76,18,"A spring there, called Salsabîl."
  77,13,"For the Day of Sorting Out (the men of Paradise from the men destined for Hell)."
  77,14,"And what will explain to you what is the Day of Sorting Out?"
  77,15,"Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)!"
  78,10,"And We have made the night as a covering (through its darkness),"
  78,11,"And We have made the day for livelihood."
  78,12,"And We have built above you seven strong (heavens),"
  79,4,"And by those that press forward as in a race (i.e. the angels or stars or the horses)."
  79,5,"And by those angels who arrange to do the Commands of their Lord, (so verily, you disbelievers will be called to account)."
  79,6,"On the Day (when the first blowing of the Trumpet is blown), the earth and the mountains will shake violently (and everybody will die)."
  80,1,"(The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم) frowned and turned away."
  80,2,"Because there came to him the blind man (i.e. ‘Abdullâh bin Umm-Maktûm, who came to the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم while he was preaching to one or some of the Quraish chiefs)."
  80,3,"And how can you know that he might become pure (from sins)?"